FocusFlow - ADHD Friendly Task Manager

FocusFlow is a minimalist, energy-aware task manager designed specifically for the ADHD brain. It prioritizes "Brain Dumping" to clear mental clutter and "Micro-stepping" to lower the barrier to starting difficult tasks.

🚀 Live Demo

You can run this project simply by opening index.html in any modern web browser.

✨ Key Features

Energy-Based Filtering: Sort tasks by Low, Medium, or High energy requirements.

Micro-steps (Subtasks): Break overwhelming tasks into tiny, manageable actions.

Focus Mode: A dedicated UI with a Pomodoro timer and a specific checklist for the task at hand.

Brain Dump Interface: Quickly capture thoughts before they disappear.

Dark Mode: Easy on the eyes for late-night hyperfocus sessions.

Privacy First: All data is stored locally in your browser (LocalStorage).

Data Portability: Export and Import your task list as JSON files.

🛠️ Technical Details

Frontend: HTML5, Tailwind CSS

Fonts: Lexend (designed for readability)

State Management: Vanilla JavaScript & LocalStorage

Deployment: Zero-build process; ready for GitHub Pages.

📂 Installation

Clone the repository:

git clone [https://github.com/your-username/focusflow.git](https://github.com/your-username/focusflow.git)


Open index.html in your browser.

